{
  "global": "Compute the average energy carried per escaping N₂ molecule via effusion by flux-weighting the Maxwell-Boltzmann distribution and adding uncorrelated internal (rotational) energy.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Identify the effusion flux-weighted speed distribution for escaping molecules",
      "atomics": [
        "State that the hole is in the effusive regime (√A ≪ λ), so molecules escape independently without collisions at the hole",
        "Write the equilibrium Maxwell-Boltzmann speed distribution f(v) ∝ v² exp(−mv²/2k_BT)",
        "Argue that the escape rate is proportional to v_x (the normal velocity component), so the flux-weighted distribution of escaping molecules is g(v) ∝ v · f(v) ∝ v³ exp(−mv²/2k_BT)",
        "Decompose the 3-D picture: v_y, v_z are unbiased Gaussian; only v_x acquires a v_x-weighting factor"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Compute the average translational kinetic energy of escaping molecules",
      "atomics": [
        "Compute ⟨v_x²⟩_eff using the v_x-weighted distribution: ∫₀^∞ v_x³ e^{−αv_x²} dv_x / ∫₀^∞ v_x e^{−αv_x²} dv_x = (1/2α²)/(1/2α) = 1/α = 2k_BT/m, giving ½m⟨v_x²⟩_eff = k_BT",
        "Note that v_y and v_z retain equilibrium averages: ½m⟨v_y²⟩ = ½m⟨v_z²⟩ = ½k_BT each",
        "Sum: ⟨KE_trans⟩_eff = k_BT + ½k_BT + ½k_BT = 2k_BT"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Determine the average internal (rotational) energy of escaping N₂ molecules",
      "atomics": [
        "State that N₂ is diatomic with 2 active rotational degrees of freedom at moderate temperatures (vibrational modes frozen out)",
        "Argue that rotational state is statistically independent of translational velocity in the Maxwell-Boltzmann distribution, so no selection bias acts on rotation",
        "Conclude ⟨E_rot⟩_eff = ⟨E_rot⟩_eq = (2/2)k_BT = k_BT"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Sum translational and rotational contributions to obtain E_avg",
      "atomics": [
        "Add: E_avg = ⟨KE_trans⟩_eff + ⟨E_rot⟩_eff = 2k_BT + k_BT = 3k_BT",
        "Sanity-check: 3k_BT > (5/2)k_BT (equilibrium average), confirming that faster-moving molecules are preferentially selected"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Verify dimensional consistency: each term is k_BT (energy units) ✓",
    "Confirm the result is independent of m and N₀, depending only on T and k_B as required by the problem statement"
  ],
  "gold_actions": {
    "global": "Apply flux-weighted Maxwell-Boltzmann effusion theory to N₂: bias the speed distribution by v (normal flux factor), evaluate ⟨KE_trans⟩_eff = 2k_BT, add ⟨E_rot⟩_eff = k_BT from uncorrelated rotational DoF, yielding E_avg = 3k_BT.",
    "subtasks": [
      {
        "subtask": "Establish the flux-weighted effusion distribution g(v) ∝ v³ exp(−mv²/2k_BT)",
        "atomics": [
          "Cite effusive condition √A ≪ λ: each molecule exits independently with no inter-molecular collisions at the orifice",
          "Write f_MB(v) = 4π(m/2πk_BT)^(3/2) v² exp(−mv²/2k_BT)",
          "Multiply by v to obtain flux-weighted distribution: g(v) ∝ v³ exp(−mv²/2k_BT)",
          "Decompose into (v_x-biased) × (unbiased v_y) × (unbiased v_z) for the component-wise calculation"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Evaluate ⟨KE_trans⟩_eff = 2k_BT via three velocity-component integrals",
        "atomics": [
          "Compute ⟨v_x²⟩_eff = [∫₀^∞ v_x³ e^{−(m/2k_BT)v_x²} dv_x] / [∫₀^∞ v_x e^{−(m/2k_BT)v_x²} dv_x] = (1/2α²)/(1/2α) = 1/α = 2k_BT/m, so ½m⟨v_x²⟩_eff = k_BT",
          "Use equilibrium averages for transverse components: ½m⟨v_y²⟩ = ½m⟨v_z²⟩ = ½k_BT",
          "Sum three contributions: ⟨KE_trans⟩_eff = k_BT + k_BT/2 + k_BT/2 = 2k_BT"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Obtain ⟨E_rot⟩_eff = k_BT by independence of rotation and translational speed",
        "atomics": [
          "Identify N₂ as a linear diatomic with 2 rotational DoF active at temperature T (vibrational modes at ~3400 K are frozen)",
          "Apply statistical independence: f_MB factorizes over translational and internal coordinates, so rotational energy distribution is unchanged by the v_x-biased selection",
          "Conclude ⟨E_rot⟩_eff = k_BT (equipartition, 2 DoF × ½k_BT)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Sum to E_avg = 3k_BT and verify",
        "atomics": [
          "E_avg = 2k_BT + k_BT = 3k_BT",
          "Check: 3k_BT > 5k_BT/2 (equilibrium per-molecule average), consistent with faster molecules escaping preferentially"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "global_atomics": [
      "Check units: k_BT has dimensions of energy [J] ✓; result contains no spurious factors of m or N₀ ✓",
      "Confirm answer depends only on k_B and T, matching the problem's instruction to express the answer in the stated fundamental constants"
    ]
  }
}
```

FINAL ANSWER: $E_{\text{avg}} = 3k_B T$
